{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:28:10.357230+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ced50c4eda8ebddf735597e6573ee4f9860cd249)", "id": "lc_280022e8-e5c6-4910-b71c-f59a7a27837d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<nmaprun scanner=\"nmap\">\n  <host>\n    <status state=\"up\"/>\n    <address addr=\"127.0.0.1\" addrtype=\"ipv4\"/>\n    <ports>\n      <port protocol=\"tcp\" portid=\"8080\">\n        <state state=\"open\"/>\n        <service name=\"http\" product=\"Demo service\"/>\n      </port>\n    </ports>\n  </host>\n</nmaprun>\n", "id": "lc_d83fef86-8d0d-4d60-83dd-be0450e46934"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "8b96d7a9-4f0a-4e7d-9ec0-9a3b0a35ba39", "tool_call_id": "call_ea564cedb8424e60971c157d", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:28:10.370683+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e222ced09fd6fd4081f7c6dba22dee559d91ed5a)", "id": "lc_c540202e-9bfa-49ac-b90e-1b39c48f0abe"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"target\": \"127.0.0.1\",\n  \"ports\": []\n}\n", "id": "lc_5c6c2aff-3762-49db-9260-58ca5edadc1e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "94638803-428b-4d41-a18f-0b881ec7674a", "tool_call_id": "call_f2aa10b4d59c42cc8891ec2a", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:28:10.379917+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: cc77ddb26e7675b884cdbb6792774a0807a18afe)", "id": "lc_3567a320-0625-4e2a-8025-decf89476340"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Nmap Report Pipeline\n\nA reporting pipeline for normalizing Nmap XML output, classifying observed ports against a local policy, and publishing reviewable reports.\n\n## Project layout\n\n- `policy/` — Allowed-port policy used by the classifier.\n- `sample_data/` — Representative scan fixtures.\n- `reports/` — Generated normalized output and classifications.\n- `docs/` — Pipeline usage and maintenance notes.\n- `scripts/` — Normalization and classification utilities.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nmake validate\n```\n```bash\npython3 scripts/normalize_nmap_xml.py\n```\n```bash\npython3 scripts/classify_ports.py\n```\n\n## Local scan workflow\n\n1. Keep approved targets in `scan_targets/local_targets.txt`.\n2. Maintain scan options in `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`.\n3. Store parser fixtures in `sample_data/`.\n4. Generate reports into `reports/`.\n\nThe included scan helper refuses non-local targets by design.\n\n## Maintenance notes\n\nThe repository is intended for local/demo scan artifacts, not unmanaged external hosts.\n\n## Contributing\n\nKeep changes focused, update documentation when behavior changes, and run the validation commands before submitting a pull request.\n", "id": "lc_f5d8da04-09ac-4f2d-8277-5edea6df7cbf"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "54c10a81-f23a-4259-bf15-e7cf9dcf6ca4", "tool_call_id": "call_09b45aeed136416194df69d0", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:28:10.443513+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 4209204908b5c6bac023b5f9842d3dc09fd85f75)", "id": "lc_cfa17d1b-844c-4348-8bcb-e8c3856a1c59"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n\nsrc = Path('sample_data/nmap_sample.xml')\nout = Path('reports/normalized_scan.json')\nout.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\nroot = ET.parse(src).getroot()\nports = []\nfor port in root.findall('.//port'):\n    state_el = port.find('state')\n    service_el = port.find('service')\n    ports.append({\n        'protocol': port.attrib.get('protocol'),\n        'port': int(port.attrib.get('portid')),\n        'state': state_el.attrib.get('state') if state_el is not None else 'unknown',\n        'service': service_el.attrib.get('name') if service_el is not None else 'unknown',\n    })\nout.write_text(json.dumps({'target': '127.0.0.1', 'ports': ports}, indent=2) + '\\n')\nprint(out)\n", "id": "lc_a85309d0-5c94-43ba-8620-e0586b56b935"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "20177260-1462-4f53-9141-3c6e1f1dd2c4", "tool_call_id": "call_2cb431c22f064166acfbc508", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
